 The Zimbabwean Police have issued a reward for
information relating to the bombing that took place on Saturday. The explosion took place in Bulawayo, Zimbabwe, moments
after Zimbabwean president Emmerson’s Mnangagwa address at an election rally. The Zimbabwean Broadcasting Corporation reported that at
least 49 people were injured and no deaths were recorded. Zimbabwean Police spokesperson Senior Assistant
Commissioner Charity Charamba, during a press briefing in Harare on Sunday
afternoon, said that a “substantial reward” has been offered to anyone with
information that could help them with the case. Charamba also said investigations to ascertain what
transpired at the stadium are currently underway. 